### Notes

*   ^ While his surname is often pronounced [/ˈkliːni/](/Help:IPA/English) KLEE-nee or [/kliːn/](/Help:IPA/English) KLEEN, Kleene himself insisted on the pronunciation [/ˈkleɪni/](/Help:IPA/English) KLAY-nee. His son, Ken Kleene, noted that this pronunciation appears to be unique. However, the surname is found in the Netherlands, where the 'ee' sound can be similar to 'ay' in "hail," albeit shorter. It's plausible Stephen Kleene was aware of this linguistic nuance. [citation needed](/Wikipedia:Citation_needed)

